defaultDavid defaultWagstaffdefault:default The commercial potential of heat networks is recognised in the market. The Green Investment Bank had always been informally working very closely with us; it is now formally stating that it is very interested in investing its own money in heat networks and leveraging other money into heat networks. We are confident that the commercials will stack up with the heat networks, which is precisely why, as the Minister said, we are not suggesting that Government money should be used to build heat 
defaultnetworks. What we are trying to do is help local authorities and others who have a strategy that involves developing a heat network to put in place all the building blocks to build a business model and to get private sector investment, and we are confident that that will happen.
defaultGregory Barker:default And I think the engagement of the Green Investment Bank on this agenda, although it is early days, is very encouraging, because this is a classic example of where the bank can address current market failure and create a new market for private sector investment by leading the way.
