defaultGregory Barker:default I think that there is perhaps more political will to address the issue and to see it as a genuine part of a broader energy strategy. There isn’t a silver bullet, so you are quite right, but the priority that CHP is getting in the Department—the resource that is being targeted on it—is greater than we have seen before, and that is partly because of that political priority that is being placed on it.
